Cloning project with git:
1) If you are using Intellij: Login to your github account (this will be used later when you want to commit or pull changes). Inellij->Settings->Version Control->Github (as shown here): intellij/Intellij_github_account.png
2) Add git tool to your machine. Use this for reference if needed: https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/quickstart/set-up-git
3) For cloning with ssh:
(when you open the below url's, please select the platform that you are using as shown in this image): ssh/ssh_select_platform.png
  i) Generate a new ssh key using terminal or cmd in your local machine: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent
  ii) Add the ssh public key to your github account: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/adding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account
  iii) Test your ssh connection in your local machine: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/testing-your-ssh-connection
4) Copy the ssh url of the github repository and clone it in your localhost machine
